properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - PORT MACQUARIE Pacific Highway at Houston Mitchell Drive
properties.otherAdvice:
One southbound lane will remain closed over a two kilometre section of the Pacific Highway until mid-February and there will be no right-hand turns into and out of Houston Mitchell Drive until late February, weather permitting.  

Motorists wanting to travel north from Houston Mitchell Drive will need to turn left to travel south along the Pacific Highway to Bago Road interchange at Herons Creek before turning north (about 7.5 kilometres one way).

Alternatively, motorists travelling to Port Macquarie from Bonny Hills can use Ocean Drive.  

Northbound motorists accessing Bonny Hills from the Pacific Highway should exit at Ocean Drive interchange at Kew (about 15 kilometres south of Houston Mitchell Drive) and travel via Laurieton and North Haven.  

An alternative route for northbound motorists accessing Bonny Hills from the Pacific Highway is via the Port Macquarie interchange.

At the intersection of the Pacific Highway and Oxley Highway, motorists can perform a U-turn to travel south along the Pacific Highway and turn left into Houston Mitchell Dive.  

Cyclists will also be restricted from turning right into and out of Houston Mitchell Drive, and travelling southbound on the Pacific Highway beyond Ryans Road.

A detour will be in place for cyclists via Burrawan Forest Drive.
